3 Pie chart

pData$Classification <- ifelse(grepl(paste("IA", "IB", "IIA", "IIB", sep = "|"), as.character(pData$UICC_TUMOR_CLASSIFICATION)), 
    "I_II", as.character(pData$UICC_TUMOR_CLASSIFICATION))
## create data
datPie <- pData %>% group_by(Subtypes, Classification) %>% summarise(Freq = length(Classification)) %>% 
    arrange(Classification) %>% na.omit()
## define groups
class <- unique(datPie$Classification)

for (i in seq_along(class)) {
    ## filtered dataclass[i],]
    filteredData <- datPie[datPie$Classification %in% class[i], ]
    ## samples
    nSamples <- sum(filteredData$Freq)
    ## add percent
    filteredData <- filteredData %>% mutate(prop = percent(Freq/nSamples))
    ## plot
    p <- filteredData %>% ggplot(aes(x = "", y = Freq)) + geom_bar(aes(fill = Subtypes), 
        width = 0.1, stat = "identity", color = "gray50") + coord_polar("y", start = 0) + 
        scale_fill_manual(values = brewer.pal(3, "Set1")) + theme_void() + labs(title = paste(class[i], 
        "n=", nSamples)) + theme(legend.title = element_blank(), legend.position = "bottom", 
        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) + guides(fill = guide_legend(ncol = 3)) + 
        theme(plot.margin = unit(c(1, 1, 1, 1), "lines")) + geom_label_repel(aes(label = prop), 
        size = 5, show.legend = F, nudge_x = 3)
    ## print
    print(p)
    ## save plot
    save_plot(paste0("../results/nmf/pieChart_", class[i], ".svg"), fig = p, width = 9, 
        height = 6, dpi = 300)
}
